line_1: And has no Man, but who has kill'd
line_2: A Father, right to get a Child?

line_1: But nobler thou, thy thousands kill'd,
line_2: With flying colours leav'st the field.

line_1: And Absalom, the lov'd ungrateful, kill'd,
line_2: When David's General had won the Field,
Than some grand Murtherer O'th' Field,

line_1: In fine, whatever Grecian Chief was kill'd,
line_2: My fearful Heart, like frigid Ice, was chill'd;

line_1: With Offal from the Meat he kill'd,
line_2: Their hungry Paunches well he fill'd:
An' L — d! if ance they pit her till't,
An' durk an' pistol at her belt,
An' rin her whittle to the hilt,
